Do you like being caught in a trap of your own illogic? I know it feels good to expose people for the trolls they are.<br>
<br>
And roamer:<br>
Yes, I played a monk (Riokan) on Rallos up to 21 before I got bored. This by no means makes me the expert on PvP, but by using my own observations, combined with comparisons of spell lines, combined with the observations of the hundreds of people I have talked to throughout my time in EQ have lead me to the conclusion that magicians are weak in PvP.  And, 20-40 do appear to be the prime PvP levels. The shift in roles doesn't happen yet, and imbalances don't begin popping up. I have had a few encounters that were exhilarating.. and a few that were aggravating. But, the three times I fought a Magician, I won by ignoring pet long enough to get that Magician to stay put and die. I got stunned twice by the pet of a level 24 magician.. but all the lower pets bounced right off of me like they weren't even there.<br>
<br>
In the higher end, the stun (and root) + dd component works against us in both PvP and PvE. I for one would rather that DD component were taken away, in exchange for a lower resist rate (or duration increase, but not both) so that they weren't so easily resisted.<br>
<br>
The fatal flaw I see in PvP is how the magic and melee systems are based upon two entirely different things, instead of being somewhat based upon the same thing. I hate comparing EQ to DAoC, but here I must. In DAoC, there are very few resists to speak of. You get bonuses versus certain things, and penalties versus certain things. And, PvP is amost 100% voluntary. I would probably play on a PvP server if only certain zones (like those far away from civilization) were pvp, and those closer were not. I mean, it only makes sense that you can kill somebody out in the middle of nowhere, but not in front of town guards.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I am rambling. There is no way to convince me that Magicians present much difficulty in PvP in the higher levels. Lower, maybe, but higher? No. Resists, and the inability of pet's to resist, make us medicore in anything but the most ideal condition. <br>
<br>
Does this mean Magicians suck? No. <br>
<br>
